=head1 DESCRIPTION

A metadata object that represents the deletion task being executed.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 ConfigurationType => Str

The type of configuration item to delete. Supported types are: SERVER.


=head2 DeletedConfigurations => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The list of configuration IDs that were successfully deleted by the
deletion task.


=head2 DeletionWarnings => ArrayRef[L<Paws::Discovery::DeletionWarning>]

A list of configuration IDs that produced warnings regarding their
deletion, paired with a warning message.


=head2 EndTime => Str

An epoch seconds timestamp (UTC) of when the deletion task was
completed or failed.


=head2 FailedConfigurations => ArrayRef[L<Paws::Discovery::FailedConfiguration>]

A list of configuration IDs that failed to delete during the deletion
task, each paired with an error message.


=head2 RequestedConfigurations => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The list of configuration IDs that were originally requested to be
deleted by the deletion task.


=head2 StartTime => Str

An epoch seconds timestamp (UTC) of when the deletion task was started.


=head2 Status => Str

The current execution status of the deletion task. Valid status are:
INITIALIZING | VALIDATING | DELETING | COMPLETED | FAILED.


=head2 TaskId => Str

The deletion task's unique identifier.



